-- Cisco to Buy NDS Group for $5 Billion, Including Debt
-- B y   W i l l   D a l e y
-- 2012-03-15T12:08:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/cisco-to-buy-nds-group-for-5-billion-including-debt.html
Cisco Systems Inc. (CSCO) , the biggest
maker of networking equipment, said it plans to buy NDS Group
Ltd. for about $5 billion, including the assumption of debt and
retention-based incentives.  The acquisition is expected to close in the second half of
2012,  San Jose , California-based Cisco said today in a
statement. NDS Group, a provider of video software, has more
than 5,000 workers and has headquarters in the U.K.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Daley at 
 wdaley2@bloomberg.net  